# Copilot instructions for this repository

## Quick commands

- Dev server (frontend):
  - cd currency-war && npm install && npm run dev
- Build (production):
  - cd currency-war && npm run build  # runs: tsc -b && vite build
- Lint (all files):
  - cd currency-war && npm run lint  # runs eslint .
  - Lint a single file: cd currency-war && npx eslint src/components/TopBar.tsx
- Playwright e2e (end-to-end):
  - Run full suite: cd currency-war && npm run test:e2e
  - Run headed: cd currency-war && npm run test:e2e:headed
  - Run a single test file: cd currency-war && npx playwright test path/to/spec.ts
  - Run a single test by name: cd currency-war && npx playwright test -g "test name"

## High-level architecture

- Frontend-only project (Vite + React + TypeScript) located in `currency-war/`.
- State management: Zustand store at `src/store/gameStore.ts`. Central single-store pattern; main exported hook is `useGameStore`.
- UI: Component tree rooted at `src/main.tsx` → `App.tsx`. Major panels:
  - TopBar, BattleBoard, ShopPanel, BenchPanel, InfoPanel (under `src/components/`).
- Data-driven design: gameplay content is in `src/data/`:
  - `heroes.ts` — Hero configs (id, cost, traits, baseStats)
  - `bonds.ts` — Bond/trait definitions and activation levels
  - `investments.ts` — Investment configs (id, tier, effect)
- Utilities: `src/utils/` contains game logic helpers (e.g., `bondCalculator.ts`) used to derive UI state from data and board state.

## Key conventions and patterns (important for Copilot)

- IDs are authoritative strings:
  - Hero ids: `h1`, `h2`, ... (use HEROES array)
  - Bond keys: use the Chinese trait names (e.g., '仙舟') as keys into `BONDS`.
  - Investment ids: `inv_1`, `inv_2`, ...
- Hero instances on bench/board use the `HeroInstance` shape from the store: `{ uuid, heroId, star }` — uuid is generated client-side.
- Shop behavior:
  - `shop.cards` is an array of heroId or `null` (card becomes `null` when bought).
  - Bench has 9 slots (Array(9).fill(null)); board has 8 slots (2 rows × 4 cols). Board capacity is gated by `player.level`.
- Bond counting:
  - `calculateActiveBonds` counts unique heroIds on the board (duplicate 1-star copies count once). See `src/utils/bondCalculator.ts` for exact logic — copy or reuse this implementation when changing UI displays.
- State transitions:
  - Game phase values: `'planning' | 'combat' | 'event' | 'gameover'` — preserve these exact strings when reading/writing state.
  - Use `useGameStore` actions (e.g., `buyHero`, `moveHero`, `startCombat`, `endCombat`) rather than mutating store objects directly.
- Cost / XP / Level arrays are centralized (see `LEVEL_XP_REQ` in `gameStore.ts`) — update there if changing level progression.

## Where to change content safely

- Add or tweak heroes / bonds / investments in `src/data/*` — UI and game logic expect those shapes.
- Keep `effect` on InvestmentConfig pure/simple and avoid side-effectful global mutations. Prefer returning patches to game state where possible.

## Files and search terms helpful to Copilot

- use these symbols to find fast: `useGameStore`, `HEROES`, `BONDS`, `INVESTMENTS`, `calculateActiveBonds`, `BenchPanel`, `BattleBoard`, `ShopPanel`.

